HEADWORD: Demibastion
<hw>Dem"i*bas"tion</hw> <pr>(?; 106)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>demi- bastion</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>A half bastion,
or that part of a bastion consisting of one face and one
flank.</def>⟦br⟧
